  "response": "Here are three important rivers in India:\n\n1. Ganges (Ganga) River\n- Considered sacred in Hinduism\n- Supports over 400 million people\n- Provides water for drinking, agriculture, and religious practices\n- Flows through major cities like Varanasi and Kolkata\n\n2. Indus River\n- Originates in Tibet and flows through northern India and Pakistan\n- Historically significant for ancient Indus Valley Civilization\n- Critical for agriculture and irrigation\n- Supports major agricultural regions\n\n3. Brahmaputra River\n- Originates in Tibet and flows through northeastern India\n- Important for agriculture and transportation\n- Supports diverse ecosystems and wildlife\n- Provides water for millions of people in the region\n\nThese rivers are crucial for India's agriculture, economy, culture, and religious practices. They support large populations, provide water resources, and have significant historical and ecological importance.",
